## Public transportation

Several public‑transit stations in Southern California bear the name **Pacific Coast Highway**, reflecting their proximity to the eponymous roadway:

- **[Pacific Coast Highway station (A Line)](/Pacific_Coast_Highway_station_(A_Line))** – a light‑rail station on the Los Angeles Metro Rail A Line, located in Long Beach.  
- **[Pacific Coast Highway station (J Line)](/Pacific_Coast_Highway_station_(J_Line))** – a Busway station on the Los Angeles Metro J Line, situated in Carson.  

These stations serve commuters traveling along the Pacific Coast corridor and are integrated into the broader regional transportation network, providing connections to other Metro lines and bus routes.

